These creatures have a level of intellect comparable to most dogs, but they have very independent spirits and are generally distrustful of creatures that aren't elves or half-elves.

Cooshee are quite effective fighters. When engaging someone in combat, cooshee often try to knock their opponent down with their large forepaws before biting them. These bites are bone-crushing, capable of felling an orc warrior. If ordered to subdue an opponent, cooshee simply close their jaws over their target's throat, resting their teeth against its skin. The threat is always clear.

Lerodan Menalrion is a moon elf with an open smile and a talent for conversation, overseeing the general goods of The Long And Short. Charismatic and personable, he enjoys engaging customers as much as completing a sale, and his easy manner has earned the shop a loyal following. His approach is relaxed but capable, giving the store its welcoming atmosphere.

Ithshariel Le'Quella is an ar-tel-quessir of refined bearing, sharp tongue and careful manners, long trained under the tutelage of House Le'Quella. Having an experienced eye for fashion, she oversees the clothier and tailor shop of Winya Ravana, known for having a practical understanding of the varied needs of the city's clientele.

Blossom Menalrion is an elfling who manages the potions and supplies with tireless care and attention. Diligent and hard working, she is rarely still, checking labels, reordering stock, and quietly correcting small details others might miss. She often fusses over Lerodan, keeping him organised and well looked after, and her steady effort ensures the shop runs as smoothly as her husband's charm suggests.
